verbose_text: Thus, Nef appears to increase NF-kappaB activity early during the viral life cycle (i.e., from viral entry to expression of Tat, Rev, and Nef from completely spliced viral RNAs) to initiate proviral transcription, whereas Vpu downmodulates NF-kappaB activity during later stages (i.e., during expression of Vpu, Vpr, Vif, and structural proteins from singly and unspliced viral RNAs) to suppress the antiviral immune response.
